n models resulting from his irreverent approach to the classics. The book sheds new light on Fletcher’s intellectual life, his vision of history, and the interconnections between these plays and the rest of his canon.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2022. 4aShakespeare 2022. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Renaissance.2bisacsh  aBonduca.  aFalse One.  aProphetess.  aShakespeare.  aTrauerspiel.  aValentinian.  aWalter Benjamin.  aclassical reception.  ahistory.  alate antiquity.1 aLovascio, Domenico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packagez978311128144540uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615739340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526157393423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526157393/original  a978-3-11-128144-5  Manchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packageb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles